      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "for the degree of Bachelor of Arts in Liberal Arts and Sciences in Anthropology, Sociocultural and Linguistic Anthropology Concentration"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "A Major Plan of Study Form must be completed and submitted to the LAS Student Affairs Office before the end of the fifth semester (60- 75 hours). Please see your adviser.",
        "credit_requirement": "75"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Departmental Distinction: The department may award distinction, high distinction, or highest distinction to any Anthropology major whose overall and major grade point averages are 3.25 or higher; and who successfully completes 33 hours of anthropology courses, including 4-6 hours of ANTH 494 and ANTH 495 resulting in an Honors Thesis. The level of distinction is based on evaluation of the honors thesis.  See the departmental academic advisor for details.",
        "course_codes": [
          "ANTH 494",
          "ANTH 495"
        ],
        "credit_requirement": "33"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "All students must discuss their selection of coursework with a departmental adviser."
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Graduation Requirements"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum hours required for graduation: 120 hours.",
        "credit_requirement": "120"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum hours required major and supporting course work: 45-48. Twelve hours of 300- and 400-level Anthropology courses must be taken on this campus.",
        "level_requirement": "400"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "University Requirements"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Minimum of 40 hours of upper-division coursework, generally at the 300- or 400-level. These hours can be drawn from all elements of the degree.  Students should consult their academic advisor for additional guidance in fulfilling this requirement.",
        "level_requirement": "400",
        "credit_requirement": "40"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "The university and residency requirements can be found in the Student Code (§ 3-801) and in the Academic Catalog."
      },
